Ada Wodu, Calabar The Cross River State Independent Electoral Commission has shifted the state local government election from February 22, 2020 to March 28, 2020. The commission’s chairman, Dr Mike Ushie, in a  statement on Monday said the decision was taken after consultation with stakeholders across the state. He said, “In line with CROSIEC Law Section 20(1) Vol. 3 Cap C18 laws of Cross River 2004 and in keeping with the provisions of the Electoral Act 2010 (as amended) which guarantees 30 and 90 days respectively for the issuance of notification of conduct of the  local government election, and in consultation with stakeholders in the electoral process held across the state and in the commission’s Conference Hall  on December 23, notice is hereby given effective today that  the Cross River State Local Government council election  shall hold on March 28, 2020.” Copyright PUNCH.
